I met my mom, who raves about this place, to eat 'Pollo a la Brasa' which is what Cholos is known for.  I have to admit after reading the reviews, I was nervous. My mother is Peruvian and we always go to these Chicken dives and find average food.  I entered to a somewhat modern decorated hole in the wall and checked out the bathrooms, which were very clean. The servers uniform was impressive as well.  I ordered 'Papa a la Huancaina' which was average, however the Chicken was very good. It was moist and seasoned nicely. Their flan was tasty and overall had a nice experience. The service was not friendly but the table was well kept. I would recommend it to anyone for a tasty "Pollo a la Brasa' or a great, quick lunch at a great price.
